Load and getting familiar with NetCDF datasets¶

Climate Geospatial Analysis on Python with Xarray - Coursera

In [1]:
import xarray as xr
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
In [2]:
ds = xr.open_dataset('data.nc')

Specify plotting parameters¶

In [3]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [10, 7]
plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 12})

Basic info about the dataset¶

expver: 2 mix of ERA5 (level 01) AND ERA5T (level 05)

Time no. steps = 500, from 1979 Jan to 2020 Aug (monthly data)

tp = total precipitation in metres

skt = surface temperature in Kelvin

lai_hv = leaf area index, high vegetation

Latitude is from 6 to -16, resolution = 0.25 degree

Longitude is from -82 to -46.75, resolution = 0.25 degree
